          {
            "name": "execute_promql_query",
            "description": "Execute an instant PromQL query against CloudWatch.\n\nReturns the current value of metrics at a single point in time (instant vector).\nFor time series over a range, use execute_promql_range_query instead.\n\nUse this tool when:\n- The user provides a PromQL expression\n- The user references OTLP-ingested metrics or labels (@resource.*, @aws.*, @instrumentation.*)\n- The user asks about enriched vended AWS metrics with OTel labels\n- The user wants to query by AWS resource tags (@aws.tag.*)\n\nUse get_metric_data instead when:\n- The user references classic CloudWatch namespaces/dimensions (AWS/EC2, etc.)\n- The user wants Metrics Insights SQL syntax\n\nPromQL label conventions (OTLP scope to label mapping):\n- @resource.{attr} - OTel resource attributes (e.g., @resource.service.name=\"myservice\")\n- @instrumentation.{attr} - instrumentation scope (e.g., @instrumentation.@name=\"cloudwatch.aws/ec2\")\n- @datapoint.{attr} or bare - datapoint attributes / CW dimensions (e.g., InstanceId=\"i-xxx\")\n- @aws.account_id, @aws.region - AWS system labels\n- @aws.tag.{Key} - AWS resource tags (e.g., @aws.tag.Environment=\"production\", @aws.tag.Team=\"backend\")\n\nFor enriched vended AWS metrics, use histogram functions\n(OTel enrichment must be enabled first: `aws cloudwatch start-otel-enrichment`):\n- histogram_avg({CPUUtilization, \"@instrumentation.@name\"=\"cloudwatch.aws/ec2\"})\n- histogram_sum({Invocations, FunctionName=\"my-func\"})\n\nLimits: max 500 series returned, 7-day range, 20s timeout.\n\nExample queries:\n- {\"http.server.active_requests\", \"@resource.service.name\"=\"myservice\"}\n- histogram_avg({CPUUtilization, \"@instrumentation.@name\"=\"cloudwatch.aws/ec2\"})\n- sum by (\"@aws.tag.Team\")(histogram_sum({Invocations, \"@instrumentation.@name\"=\"cloudwatch.aws/lambda\"}))\n",
            "disabled": false,
            "inputSchema": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {
                "query": {
                  "description": "The PromQL query to execute",
                  "title": "Query",
                  "type": "string"
                },
                "time": {
                  "anyOf": [
                    {
                      "type": "string"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "null"
                    }
                  ],
                  "default": null,
                  "description": "Evaluation timestamp (RFC3339 or Unix timestamp). Defaults to current time.",
                  "title": "Time"
                },
                "region": {
                  "anyOf": [
                    {
                      "type": "string"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "null"
                    }
                  ],
                  "default": null,
                  "description": "AWS region. Defaults to AWS_REGION env or us-east-1. PromQL is available in: us-east-1, us-west-2, eu-west-1, ap-southeast-1, ap-southeast-2.",
                  "title": "Region"
                },
                "profile_name": {
                  "anyOf": [
                    {
                      "type": "string"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "null"
                    }
                  ],
                  "default": null,
                  "description": "AWS CLI Profile Name. Falls back to AWS_PROFILE env or default credential chain.",
                  "title": "Profile Name"
                }
              },
              "required": [
                "query"
              ],
              "title": "execute_promql_queryArguments"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "execute_promql_range_query",
            "description": "Execute a PromQL range query against CloudWatch.\n\nReturns time series data over a time range (matrix). Use for trend analysis and graphs.\n\nUse this tool when:\n- The user provides a PromQL expression and wants data over a time window\n- The user references OTLP-ingested metrics or labels (@resource.*, @aws.*, @instrumentation.*)\n- The user asks about enriched vended AWS metrics with OTel labels\n\nUse get_metric_data instead when:\n- The user references classic CloudWatch namespaces/dimensions (AWS/EC2, etc.)\n- The user wants Metrics Insights SQL syntax\n\nFor enriched vended AWS metrics, use histogram functions\n(OTel enrichment must be enabled first: `aws cloudwatch start-otel-enrichment`):\n- histogram_avg({CPUUtilization, \"@instrumentation.@name\"=\"cloudwatch.aws/ec2\"})\n- histogram_sum({Errors, \"@instrumentation.@name\"=\"cloudwatch.aws/lambda\", \"@aws.tag.Team\"=\"backend\"})\n\nLimits: max 500 series, max 7-day range (including lookback), 20s timeout.\n\nExample:\n    query: 'avg_over_time({\"http.server.active_requests\", \"@resource.service.name\"=\"myservice\"}[5m])'\n    start: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n    end: \"2024-01-01T01:00:00Z\"\n    step: \"5m\"\n",
            "disabled": false,
